flowchart TD
    A[Input MNIST x<br/>Shape: B x 1 x 28 x 28] --> B[Flatten start_dim=1<br/>Output: B x 784<br/>Formula: 1*28*28 = 784]
    B --> C[Linear fc1 784 to 1024<br/>Output: B x 1024<br/>Params: 784*1024 + 1024 = 803840]
    C --> D[ReLU<br/>Output: B x 1024]
    D --> E[Dropout p=0.5<br/>Output: B x 1024]
    E --> F[Linear fc2 1024 to 128<br/>Output: B x 128<br/>Params: 1024*128 + 128 = 131200]
    F --> G[ReLU<br/>Output: B x 128]
    G --> H[Dropout p=0.5<br/>Output: B x 128]
    H --> I[Linear fc3 128 to 10<br/>Output: B x 10 logits<br/>Params: 128*10 + 10 = 1290]

    P1[Total learnable params<br/>803840 + 131200 + 1290 = 936330]
    D1[Dataset note<br/>MNIST uses 28x28 grayscale digits, so input dims are 1x28x28 and classes are 10 digits.]
    C1[Why use this model<br/>Best first baseline: very simple, fast, and good for understanding logits and CE loss.]
    S1[Shortcoming<br/>No spatial inductive bias; flattening loses local stroke structure and translation robustness.]

    I -.-> P1
    A -.-> D1
    P1 -.-> C1
    S1 -.-> C1
